<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>

<activity xml:id="act-escribirlosComoFracciones" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Escribámoslos como fracciones</title>

<statement>
  <p>Completa la tabla con tu grupo. En cada columna, escribe fracciones que sean equivalentes al número entero de la primera fila.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>Paso 1: Escribe dos fracciones que sean equivalentes a cada número entero (seis fracciones en total). Pasa tu hoja a tu derecha.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Paso 2: Cuando recibas la hoja de tu compañero, escribe una fracción nueva que sea equivalente a uno de los números enteros.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Repitan el paso 2 hasta que la tabla esté completa.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <sidebyside widths="45% 45%">
    <tabular top="medium" halign="center" valign="middle">
      <col width="33%"/>
      <col width="33%"/>
      <col width="34%"/>
      <row header="yes" left="medium" bottom="medium">
        <cell right="medium">4</cell>
        <cell right="medium">5</cell>
        <cell right="medium">6</cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{4}}{\large{1}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\phantom{\huge000}}{\large{2}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\phantom{\huge000}}{\large{3}}</m></p></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\phantom{\huge000}}{\large{4}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>        
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{30}}{\large{6}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><nbsp/></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{48}}{\large{8}}</m></p></cell>
      </row>
    </tabular>
    <image source="png-source/CS 3.5.C Lesson 13 Activity 2.png" width="40%" component="web">
      <shortdescription>niños mirando lienzo donde dice que 2 es igual a 4/2</shortdescription>
    </image>
  </sidebyside>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Sample completed table:</p>
    <tabular top="medium" halign="center" valign="middle">
      <col width="33%"/>
      <col width="33%"/>
      <col width="34%"/>
      <row header="yes" left="medium" bottom="medium">
        <cell right="medium">4</cell>
        <cell right="medium">5</cell>
        <cell right="medium">6</cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{4}}{\large{1}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{5}}{\large{1}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{6}}{\large{1}}</m></p></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{8}}{\large{2}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{10}}{\large{2}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{12}}{\large{2}}</m></p></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{12}}{\large{3}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{15}}{\large{3}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{18}}{\large{3}}</m></p></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{16}}{\large{4}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{20}}{\large{4}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{24}}{\large{4}}</m></p></cell>        
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{24}}{\large{6}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{30}}{\large{6}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{36}}{\large{6}}</m></p></cell>
      </row>
      <row left="minor" bottom="minor">
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{32}}{\large{8}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{40}}{\large{8}}</m></p></cell>
        <cell right="minor"><p><m>\frac{\large{48}}{\large{8}}</m></p></cell>
      </row>
    </tabular>
  </solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-actividad-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li> 
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-3-NF-A-3-c" text="custom">3.NF.A.3.c</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>15 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this activity is for students to write whole numbers as fractions. Students may reason in any way that makes sense to them, including using patterns they noticed previously. When students observe patterns as they write whole numbers as fractions, they look for and make use of structure (MP7).</p>
    <p>This activity uses a <q>carousel</q> structure in which students complete a rotation of tasks. Consider demonstrating the steps before students begin.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Groups of 3</li>
      <li>
        <q>Tómense un momento para examinar la tabla y los números que hay en ella. ¿Cómo piensan que funciona la tabla?</q>
      </li>
      <li>1 minute: quiet think time</li>
      <li>Share responses.</li>
      <li>
        <q>En su grupo, por turnos, expliquen por qué <m>\frac{4}{1}</m> es equivalente a 4, <m>\frac{30}{6}</m> es equivalente a 5 y <m>\frac{48}{8}</m> es equivalente a 6</q>
      </li>
      <li>2 minutes: group discussion</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Trabajen en grupo para completar la tabla. Comiencen por escribir dos fracciones que sean equivalentes a cada número entero: 4, 5 y 6</q>
      </li>
      <li>2 minutes: independent work time</li>
      <li>
        <q>Pasen su hoja a su derecha. En la hoja que reciben, escriban una fracción nueva que sea equivalente a uno de los número enteros, el que elijan</q>
      </li>
      <li>
        <q>Sigan pasando y escribiendo una fracción adicional que sea equivalente a uno de los números enteros hasta que la tabla esté completa</q>
      </li>
      <li>Encourage students to ask clarifying questions before they begin.</li>
      <li>7–8 minutes: group work time</li>
      <li>
        <q>Prepárense para explicar cómo saben qué fracciones escribir para cada número entero</q>
      </li>
      <li><p>Monitor for students who:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>use a number line (either draw a new one or extending those from an earlier activity)</li>
          <li>extend a pattern they noticed in fractions that are equivalent to whole numbers</li>
          <li>use multiplication facts</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <postlude> (se pueden mostrar después del enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<postlude component="profesor">

  <!-- Estrategias de apoyo para estudiantes con dificultades -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="support-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>If students don’t write a whole number as a fraction, consider asking:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <q>Dime cómo escribirías 1 como una fracción</q>
      </li>
      <li>
        <q>¿Cómo puedes usar la fracción que es equivalente a 1 para escribir este número como una fracción?</q>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Síntesis de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Invite a group of students to display their completed table.</li>
      <li>Select previously identified students to share how they knew what fractions to write for each whole number.</li>
      <li>Invite the class to share other strategies for generating equivalent fractions.</li>
      <li><p><q>¿Qué patrones nuevos observan en la tabla que ya completaron?</q> (Sample responses:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>In fractions that are equivalent to 4, you can get the numerator by skip-counting by the denominator 4 times.</li>
          <li>In the row with thirds, the numerator increases by 3. In the row for fourths, it increases by 4.)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>


  <!-- Descripción del desarrollo de lenguaje matemático -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="language-actividad-titulo"/></title><p>[++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p><em>MLR8 Discussion Supports.</em> Synthesis: During group presentations, invite the student(s) who are not speaking to follow along and point to the corresponding parts of the display.</p>
    <p>
      <em>Advances: Speaking, Representing</em>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>

</postlude>

</activity>